amily:Arial; font-size:12pt">There are some cycle paths in the area where I live b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ut they are unsuitable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for adult / competent cyclists</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> who wish to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">cycle distances or at much above walking pace.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I would like to see a high publicity safety and awareness campaign, with the backing of both government and police, aimed at establishing th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e right of cyclists to use the national road network and re enforcing the responsibility in law of taking due c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are and attention while driving.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A clear and unequivocal statement from the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Prime</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> minister would make a good start.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I realize that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">recent </span><span style="